description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a high calibre candidate to play an integral role in the JRU and Cancer Division at Royal National Orthopaedic Hospital. The Division is committed to providing excellent patient care, improving quality and ensuring a positive patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be accountable for providing confident and credible operational leadership and effectively deliver the operational, quality and financial priorities of the Division while working collaboratively with the professional leads in the service. There is a key focus on delivering patient access targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to deliver service changes within a complex and dynamic operational environment. Excellent people management skills and resilience are fundamental skills required for these roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working collaboratively across boundaries you will develop and motivate a large team. You must be self-motivated and work proactively at pace - managing your time, workload and priorities. You should be highly analytical and confident to challenge the status quo while building excellent working relationships that quickly enable you to become a trusted and credible leader across all staff groups&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bernie SAMAVATI - berniesamavati@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
